This article is a presidential proclamation made by Barack Obama on United Nations Day, which is celebrated on October 24th. In the proclamation, Obama highlights the importance of the United Nations as an institution that aims to prevent conflict, promote human rights, and foster global cooperation. He emphasizes the role of the United Nations in addressing global issues such as public health, economic development, climate change, terrorism, and nuclear proliferation. Obama also mentions the significance of democratic movements and the pursuit of freedom and prosperity. He states that peace is not just the absence of war, but also involves promoting stability and defending the rights of all peoples and nations. The proclamation calls on the governors of the 50 states and officials of other areas under the United States flag to observe United Nations Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.